70
00:03:19,549 --> 00:03:21,107
[COUGHING]

71
00:03:23,753 --> 00:03:25,744
- All right, any dizziness, slurred speech?
- No.

72
00:03:25,889 --> 00:03:27,083
- Yes.
- Seth.

73
00:03:27,223 --> 00:03:29,088
Will you please
tell my son that I'm fine?

74
00:03:29,225 --> 00:03:31,318
You still have weakness
in your right side,

75
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:34,897
and a persistent visual-field defect.
I'm concerned.

76
00:03:35,031 --> 00:03:37,659
- Tell her she needs to move.
- I'm not moving to Florida.

77
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,462
- I can take care of you there.
- I can take care of myself here.

78
00:03:40,603 --> 00:03:41,729
Right?

79
00:03:41,871 --> 00:03:43,998
Well, you're still at risk
for another stroke.

80
00:03:44,207 --> 00:03:46,437
- You should be with someone.
- You ganging up on me?

81
00:03:46,576 --> 00:03:49,044
You know, since Dad died,
you barely wanna talk on the phone.

82
00:03:49,178 --> 00:03:50,975
- That's not true. It's not true.
- It is.

83
00:03:51,114 --> 00:03:54,914
He thinks I'm depressed. I'm not.
I have friends. I'm not alone.

84
00:03:55,051 --> 00:03:56,780
Not family. You should be with family.

85
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,012
This is a big decision.

86
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:00,714
Deciding to move,
uproot your life, it's huge,

87
00:04:00,857 --> 00:04:03,519
but losing a spouse is huge too.

88
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,651
Do me a favor, Cynthia.
Speak with our therapist.

89
00:04:05,929 --> 00:04:07,692
It would make me feel
a lot more comfortable.

90
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:09,229
[SIGHS]

91
00:04:12,535 --> 00:04:15,629
I thought I was okay with it,
but I'm not sure if I am okay with it.

92
00:04:16,906 --> 00:04:18,396
I'm sleeping with two men.

93
00:04:18,541 --> 00:04:20,509
- Do I get a lecture now?
- Yes.

94
00:04:21,611 --> 00:04:23,169
Yes, you do.

95
00:04:27,417 --> 00:04:29,044
This is good.

96
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:30,345
- This is progress.
- Really?

97
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:33,985
- That's my lecture?
- It's fun, it's exciting, it's...

98
00:04:34,123 --> 00:04:35,818
Congratulations, man.

99
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:38,689
You're okay with it? Because
the weird thing is I'm okay with it.

100
00:04:38,828 --> 00:04:41,888
Except for the part of me
that thinks I shouldn't be, but I think I am.

101
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:45,228
Sex is good. Relationships are bad.

102
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:49,361
Relationships are what cause people
to be cold and lying and deceitful.

103
00:04:49,505 --> 00:04:52,303
- You're a therapist.
- Okay, professionally, I'd dispute that,

104
00:04:52,442 --> 00:04:54,171
and suggest you need to see
your therapist,

105
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:55,777
but personally, yes.

106
00:04:55,912 --> 00:04:58,346
As a red-blooded American,
sex is your birthright.

107
00:04:58,481 --> 00:05:02,110
- Go forth, enjoy, guilt-free.
- I will.

108
00:05:02,251 --> 00:05:03,809
I will exercise my right.

109
00:05:03,953 --> 00:05:05,682
[DOOR OPENS]

110
00:05:06,189 --> 00:05:08,384
Sorry to interrupt.
The CF results are back.

111
00:05:08,524 --> 00:05:09,957
How bad?

112
00:05:12,362 --> 00:05:17,891
If this is serious, if I'm gonna die,
please, just tell me now.

113
00:05:18,034 --> 00:05:19,763
- Ahem.
- Daron, your test came back fine.

114
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,426
It's Gracie.

115
00:05:21,938 --> 00:05:24,429
She tested positive
for Burkholderia cepacia.

116
00:05:25,008 --> 00:05:28,705
- It's a bacteria that gets in...
- Yeah, I know what it is.

117
00:05:30,179 --> 00:05:31,942
- I'm sorry.
DARON: No.

118
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:34,413
Gotta be some kind of mistake.
She looks fine. Look at her.

119
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:37,280
You're not gonna tell me
that her lung function is going downhill.

120
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:40,116
From her test results,
it appears that it already has.

121
00:05:40,256 --> 00:05:44,022
I mean, you know how contagious
this bacteria can be for CF patients.

122
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:47,061
It's a miracle that you and Julian
haven't caught it.

123
00:05:47,196 --> 00:05:49,562
What we need to do now
is get Gracie to the hospital,

124
00:05:49,699 --> 00:05:52,259
get her into isolation
while we figure out what to do.

125
00:05:52,402 --> 00:05:54,893
Okay. All right, I'll take her there now.

126
00:05:55,038 --> 00:05:57,438
No, Daron, you can't take her.

127
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:00,704
You can't touch her,
you can't be with her, or you'll die.

128
00:06:09,652 --> 00:06:14,589
I'm not being stubborn.
I don't want to move.

129
00:06:14,724 --> 00:06:16,555
Moving to a new city at any age
is stressful,

130
00:06:17,927 --> 00:06:20,862
but just for a minute,
let's look at the other side.

131
00:06:21,364 --> 00:06:22,922
Could this move be good for you?

132
00:06:23,332 --> 00:06:25,391
I can't move,

133
00:06:25,535 --> 00:06:30,131
and I can't talk to him
about why I can't move.

134
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,806
And he's not going to take no
for an answer,

135
00:06:36,546 --> 00:06:40,915
[CRYING]
And now he has Sam on his side.

136
00:06:42,518 --> 00:06:44,816
Well, you can talk to me.

137
00:06:45,555 --> 00:06:46,749
No.

138
00:06:46,889 --> 00:06:50,950
If Seth finds out the truth,
he's gonna hate me.

139
00:06:51,094 --> 00:06:53,824
Cynthia, anything you tell me
stays with me.

140
00:06:53,963 --> 00:06:55,021
Let me help you.

141
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:56,995
Talk to me.

142
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:02,270
I can't even tell Sam.

143
00:07:05,641 --> 00:07:09,202
If I can't come near you,
how are you gonna take care of me?

144
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:11,745
We'll figure something out, honey,
okay? I promise.

145
00:07:11,914 --> 00:07:15,850
But for right now, you're gonna have to go
to the hospital with Dr. Freedman, okay?

146
00:07:23,659 --> 00:07:25,286
She needs me.

147
00:07:25,428 --> 00:07:27,862
You can't put yourself at risk, or Julian.

148
00:07:27,997 --> 00:07:30,227
If either of you gets exposed,
this will kill you.

149
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:32,129
So I just leave her alone?

150
00:07:32,268 --> 00:07:34,361
Isn't there a family member
you could call?

151
00:07:34,504 --> 00:07:36,529
Someone who could help you,
could be with Gracie?

152
00:07:36,672 --> 00:07:39,402
I've got a sister in Nashville,
but she doesn't really know Gracie.

153
00:07:39,742 --> 00:07:43,178
Gracie needs me, okay? I need her.

154
00:07:44,013 --> 00:07:45,708
She's already lost her mother.
You know?

155
00:07:45,848 --> 00:07:47,315
I'm all she has.

156
00:07:47,917 --> 00:07:51,683
Look, I could wear a mask, right?
You know, we could take precautions.

157
00:07:51,821 --> 00:07:54,654
Daron, if you live together,
you will get this,

158
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:56,348
and there is no way we can treat it.

159
00:07:56,492 --> 00:07:58,858
Well, I need to be there
for both of them.

160
00:07:59,695 --> 00:08:01,822
Yeah, they both need me.

161
00:08:03,866 --> 00:08:05,993
How am I supposed to choose?

162
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,135
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

163
00:08:15,845 --> 00:08:17,540
- I'll be back.
- Okay, take care.

164
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:23,114
Hey, how's Gracie?

165
00:08:23,252 --> 00:08:25,243
Oh, you know, not good.

166
00:08:25,388 --> 00:08:27,515
Trying to be brave,
but she doesn't like the hospital.

167
00:08:27,657 --> 00:08:28,988
I don't think she understands it.

168
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:33,061
Not seeing her dad or her brother,
not living with them, that's permanent.

169
00:08:34,564 --> 00:08:36,361
What were you talking
to Charlotte about?

170
00:08:36,499 --> 00:08:39,730
Oh, she asked me to do her rounds while
she goes to Alabama to see her dad.

171
00:08:39,869 --> 00:08:42,963
What, like you owe her a favor
after what she did to us?

172
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,766
Cooper, her father is dying.

173
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:58,052
I'm sorry about your dad.

174
00:08:58,187 --> 00:09:00,314
- If there's anything you need...
- I'm fine.

175
00:09:00,756 --> 00:09:02,246
I see death every day on the job.

176
00:09:02,391 --> 00:09:04,120
It's a part of life and I'll deal with it.

177
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,421
I'm late for my flight.

178
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:12,165
Cynthia is fully capable of making
decisions about her own care.

179
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:14,462
You're not at all concerned
that a 70-year-old woman

180
00:09:14,604 --> 00:09:18,631
still recovering from a stroke is putting
herself further at risk by living alone?

181
00:09:18,774 --> 00:09:20,674
- Sam, you asked me to evaluate her.
- Yeah.

182
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:23,779
She's not depressed. She is not clinging
irrationally to her independence.

183
00:09:23,913 --> 00:09:27,314
She has legitimate reasons
for what she's doing.

184
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:29,441
- Which are?
- Privileged.

185
00:09:31,621 --> 00:09:33,384
[GROANS]

186
00:09:33,889 --> 00:09:36,016
- Hey. Um...
- Hey.

187
00:09:36,892 --> 00:09:39,588
I think it's confusing to Maya,

188
00:09:39,729 --> 00:09:41,754
meeting a woman
that you've just started to date.

189
00:09:41,897 --> 00:09:45,560
- What?
- A new girlfriend could be scary for her.

190
00:09:45,701 --> 00:09:46,963
You have a problem with Sonya?

191
00:09:47,103 --> 00:09:48,365
No, no.

192
00:09:48,504 --> 00:09:49,994
You date whoever you want.

193
00:09:50,139 --> 00:09:53,199
Just think about how this affects Maya.

194
00:09:58,114 --> 00:10:00,810
WOMAN [OVER P.A.]:
<i>Dr. Milton, 2631.</i>

195
00:10:05,421 --> 00:10:06,888
- Oh!
- Whoa.

196
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:09,389
That was almost the highlight
of my day.

197
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:11,356
Not in the mood.

198
00:10:11,494 --> 00:10:13,121
Cute kid.

199
00:10:14,797 --> 00:10:16,662
What? I can't feel for a patient?

200
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,692
Try me.

201
00:10:18,834 --> 00:10:21,234
Nine-year-old with cystic fibrosis,
patient.

202
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,497
Rare bacterial infection in her lungs.

203
00:10:23,639 --> 00:10:26,130
Father can't be with her anymore
because he has CF too.

204
00:10:26,275 --> 00:10:27,833
Same thing with her 2-year-old brother,

205
00:10:27,977 --> 00:10:30,844
because if either of them get infected
with the bacteria, they'll die.

206
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:33,210
So father has to choose:

207
00:10:34,183 --> 00:10:40,918
Let his girl die alone or stay with her
and leave a 2-year-old with CF behind.

208
00:10:42,658 --> 00:10:43,989
Burkholderia cepacia?

209
00:10:45,961 --> 00:10:47,292
What?

210
00:10:47,430 --> 00:10:50,399
I've had cancer patients manifest
the same bacterial complications

211
00:10:50,533 --> 00:10:51,693
as those with B. Cepacia.

212
00:10:51,834 --> 00:10:54,166
I've had success eradicating
the infection.

213
00:10:54,303 --> 00:10:56,828
Okay, no one in the world
has found a cure for cepacia syndrome,

214
00:10:56,972 --> 00:10:58,405
but you're gonna pitch me one?

215
00:10:58,541 --> 00:11:01,874
I know cancer's a lot different
than cystic fibrosis,

216
00:11:02,011 --> 00:11:04,912
and bacteria is more drug-resistant,
I just...

217
00:11:07,316 --> 00:11:09,375
It's a tragic story.

218
00:11:09,785 --> 00:11:11,844
- Worth a shot.
- Why would you help me?

219
00:11:12,221 --> 00:11:13,518
I'm a doctor.

220
00:11:16,859 --> 00:11:21,057
So I've spoken to your mother, Seth,

221
00:11:21,197 --> 00:11:25,224
and she is not ready to move.

222
00:11:26,202 --> 00:11:29,899
- Mom...
- If you won't listen to me, listen to her.

223
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:31,233
She understands.

224
00:11:31,374 --> 00:11:34,036
She has agreed to come in
for weekly checkups with Sam

225
00:11:34,176 --> 00:11:35,643
and counseling with me,

226
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:38,246
and to put a MedicAlert system
in her house.

227
00:11:38,381 --> 00:11:42,078
And if her condition worsens,
then we can always revisit this.

228
00:11:42,218 --> 00:11:43,810
I promised...

229
00:11:45,755 --> 00:11:48,724
I promised Dad
I would take care of you.

230
00:11:51,494 --> 00:11:56,761
Most of my friends, the idea of a parent
moving in is terrifying. We want you.

231
00:11:56,899 --> 00:11:58,764
- Seth.
- Not like I wanna put you in a home.

232
00:11:58,901 --> 00:12:01,392
- Please, Seth, stop pushing me.
- Then help me understand.

233
00:12:01,537 --> 00:12:03,664
You hate this city,
you hate the traffic, the crime.

234
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,933
- Talk to me.
- Easy, Seth.

235
00:12:06,075 --> 00:12:08,009
- I think I need a...
- Uh...

236
00:12:08,611 --> 00:12:11,171
- Mom?
- I got her legs.

237
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:12,940
VIOLET:
Get an ambulance, please.

238
00:12:13,082 --> 00:12:14,344
Is she having another stroke?

239
00:12:14,950 --> 00:12:16,941
Is she having another stroke?

240
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:20,188
SAM:
It was a transient ischemic attack.

241
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:22,449
Press. A warning sign for a stroke.

242
00:12:22,591 --> 00:12:24,684
It happened because I got upset.

243
00:12:24,827 --> 00:12:26,658
That's all. I am fine.

244
00:12:26,796 --> 00:12:29,788
You're not a doctor.
Your doctors are saying you're not fine.

245
00:12:29,932 --> 00:12:31,263
[DOOR OPENS]

246
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,668
Hey, I came as soon as I could.

247
00:12:33,803 --> 00:12:38,069
- I'm fine. Everyone is making a fuss.
- You're not fine. Hi, Annette.

248
00:12:38,207 --> 00:12:39,333
- Hey, Seth.
SETH: Thank you.

249
00:12:39,475 --> 00:12:42,273
Can you just wait outside?
We're discussing things with the doctors.

250
00:12:42,411 --> 00:12:45,209
She can stay.
I want someone on my side.

251
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:46,644
It's not about sides.

252
00:12:46,949 --> 00:12:48,940
I'm sorry, I can't...

253
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:53,977
I'm moving you out.
I'll get a lawyer if I have to.

254
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:55,721
Talk to him.

255
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,621
Talk to your son.

256
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,818
He'll understand.

257
00:12:59,495 --> 00:13:00,860
Violet, what's going on?

258
00:13:01,464 --> 00:13:03,728
She's right.
It's gotta be better than this.

259
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:08,935
[INHALES DEEPLY]

260
00:13:09,605 --> 00:13:11,903
I'm not alone.

261
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:16,041
I have someone here

262
00:13:16,178 --> 00:13:20,706
who loves me
and who wants to take care of me,

263
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:26,516
and I was afraid to tell you
because I love you too,

264
00:13:26,856 --> 00:13:30,053
and I'm afraid you won't understand.

265
00:13:30,192 --> 00:13:31,819
Understand what?

266
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:38,897
I have someone.

267
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:45,231
Your mother's in love.

268
00:13:46,108 --> 00:13:48,303
She has someone here
that she doesn't wanna leave

269
00:13:48,444 --> 00:13:50,742
and she was afraid to tell you.

270
00:14:01,891 --> 00:14:03,688
I get that you've been alone.

271
00:14:03,826 --> 00:14:05,885
I get that since Dad's been gone,
it's confusing

272
00:14:06,028 --> 00:14:07,996
and you need
to have somebody here with you.

273
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:09,222
This is not who you are.

274
00:14:09,365 --> 00:14:12,596
This isn't a reaction to your father dying.
- I'm not talking to you.

275
00:14:12,735 --> 00:14:17,035
- Seth.
- This is some grief-stricken reaction.

276
00:14:17,172 --> 00:14:20,198
No, no, we've been together for years.

277
00:14:24,146 --> 00:14:25,204
When you were with Dad?

278
00:14:25,347 --> 00:14:26,871
Yeah.

279
00:14:27,016 --> 00:14:29,541
- I am so sorry.
- You cheated on Dad with her?

280
00:14:30,352 --> 00:14:32,047
Seth.

281
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:36,014
SAM:
Seth.

282
00:14:43,732 --> 00:14:48,226
You wanna catch a movie after,
just get away from it all?

283
00:14:48,537 --> 00:14:51,005
I can't. CF research to do.

284
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:53,233
Wow, begins the day, ends the day.

285
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:55,366
I've got a little girl
who's about to die, Kevin.

286
00:14:55,511 --> 00:14:57,502
It's hard to think about going out
and relaxing.

287
00:14:59,281 --> 00:15:01,841
You could have called.
You could have said, "Don't come over."

288
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:04,145
- You wanted me to cancel?
- You're giving me attitude.

289
00:15:04,286 --> 00:15:06,618
- I'm here.
- There are other things I could be doing.

290
00:15:06,755 --> 00:15:09,315
I get a lot of invitations.
My friends, women...

291
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:11,551
So, what,
you wanna date other women?

292
00:15:11,894 --> 00:15:13,293
Maybe I do, but I don't.

293
00:15:14,096 --> 00:15:18,260
I'm not, because this is so much fun.

294
00:15:18,734 --> 00:15:20,361
[SIGHS]

295
00:15:22,605 --> 00:15:24,937
What happened to us? I mean,

296
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:28,533
there was a time when you'd eat noodles
off of my naked body.

297
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:29,939
What?

298
00:15:31,647 --> 00:15:33,410
What happened to us?

299
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:40,079
Look, I'm sorry. I thought...

300
00:15:40,222 --> 00:15:43,521
I usually think
that honesty is for the best.

301
00:15:43,659 --> 00:15:45,092
Hmm.

302
00:15:45,227 --> 00:15:48,355
Well, I knew at 15,

303
00:15:48,797 --> 00:15:53,962
but back then,
that was not what you did.

304
00:15:54,103 --> 00:15:58,972
You found a guy, got married, had kids.

305
00:16:00,676 --> 00:16:02,667
And I loved him.

306
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:04,770
I did.

307
00:16:06,682 --> 00:16:08,149
And then I met Annette,

308
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:11,747
and our kids were the same age,

309
00:16:12,488 --> 00:16:14,854
and she was...

310
00:16:15,824 --> 00:16:18,816
I couldn't stop myself.

311
00:16:20,729 --> 00:16:23,197
Well, you were honest with yourself.

312
00:16:23,932 --> 00:16:28,266
That's sometimes the hardest piece.

313
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:31,831
He's got to understand, right?

314
00:16:31,974 --> 00:16:35,341
I mean, once he gets over the shock.

315
00:16:35,477 --> 00:16:36,535
He loves you.

316
00:16:36,679 --> 00:16:39,443
He wanted to do what was best for you.

317
00:16:40,182 --> 00:16:41,877
He'll come around.

318
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:48,451
Electrons that detach
and move around are called?

319
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:51,858
- Atoms?
- Free electrons.

320
00:16:54,396 --> 00:16:55,761
Why are you being so nice to me?

321
00:16:55,898 --> 00:16:58,423
When's the last time you gave me
answers without torturing me?

322
00:16:58,567 --> 00:17:02,799
I just know you didn't have a chance
to study last night.

323
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:04,064
Okay.

324
00:17:04,206 --> 00:17:05,867
What do you wanna know about her?

325
00:17:06,008 --> 00:17:08,203
- Sonya.
- Ha-ha. I wasn't...

326
00:17:09,545 --> 00:17:11,137
- How was last night?
- It was fun.

327
00:17:12,147 --> 00:17:13,705
It wasn't uncomfortable?

328
00:17:13,849 --> 00:17:15,817
Because, you know,
you do not have to hang out

329
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:17,816
with your dad and his new girlfriend.

330
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:20,387
I like her, Mom,
and Dad really likes her.

331
00:17:20,522 --> 00:17:22,683
You'd like her too,
if you got to know her.

332
00:17:22,825 --> 00:17:25,350
Don't worry about me.
Dad's just having fun.

333
00:17:25,494 --> 00:17:26,984
You should have fun too.

334
00:17:28,864 --> 00:17:30,991
You need to get a life.

335
00:17:37,272 --> 00:17:40,264
- Pete.
- I can't stop thinking about you.

336
00:17:53,255 --> 00:17:54,779
She loves Sonya.

337
00:17:54,923 --> 00:17:59,417
And why shouldn't she?
She's smart, she is pretty and she is fun.

338
00:17:59,561 --> 00:18:01,358
She brings over movies and popcorn.

339
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:03,988
And I just... I do homework.

340
00:18:04,133 --> 00:18:06,727
Nai, you're her mom.
You're supposed to do homework,

341
00:18:06,869 --> 00:18:09,702
and Sonya is being fun because
she's trying to make a good impression.

342
00:18:10,672 --> 00:18:12,902
That's what happens
when things are new.

343
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,474
You go out of your way to be nice.

344
00:18:14,610 --> 00:18:17,204
Look at me and Kevin, you know?

345
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:19,610
Not so new, not so nice anymore.

346
00:18:19,748 --> 00:18:21,545
- That sounds like marriage.
- Ha.

347
00:18:22,951 --> 00:18:24,441
You gonna end it?

348
00:18:24,787 --> 00:18:27,881
Hey. I've been through
all of Wyatt's research.

349
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:29,217
It's pretty convincing.

350
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:32,816
- Wyatt?
- Yeah. He had an idea to help.

351
00:18:32,961 --> 00:18:35,828
Let's go find Pete and Coop.

352
00:18:41,670 --> 00:18:43,399
So I could get her back?

353
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:45,530
It's a long shot, Daron,
but we'd like to try.

354
00:18:45,674 --> 00:18:47,471
It's not gonna hurt?
I don't wanna hurt her.

355
00:18:47,609 --> 00:18:49,702
Her lungs are already full,
so we have to clear them.

356
00:18:49,845 --> 00:18:52,143
It's the same procedure.
We take a sample of the bacteria.

357
00:18:52,281 --> 00:18:54,010
We know that it worked on cancer.

358
00:18:54,349 --> 00:18:57,546
We are hoping, really hoping,
it can help Gracie.

359
00:18:57,786 --> 00:18:59,219
[SIGHS]

360
00:18:59,922 --> 00:19:03,824
You know, she loves horses.
Her whole room is horses.

361
00:19:03,959 --> 00:19:08,919
And I thought if she had these here
in her room, that she'd feel more...

362
00:19:10,499 --> 00:19:11,932
[SIGHS]

363
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:14,558
I don't know. I'll go call her.

364
00:19:14,703 --> 00:19:16,330
I'll tell her maybe.

365
00:19:20,976 --> 00:19:23,376
Delivery for Miss Gracie Rousakis.

366
00:19:29,351 --> 00:19:31,285
He's worried about me.

367
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:32,887
I don't like it when he worries.

368
00:19:33,021 --> 00:19:36,013
- Well, he's your dad. It's his job to worry.
- Tell him I'm fine.

369
00:19:36,158 --> 00:19:38,388
- Gracie...
- Make him stop worrying about me.

370
00:19:39,194 --> 00:19:41,128
Since Mom died, he's done everything.

371
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:44,130
But when he starts worrying,
he starts coughing, and then...

372
00:19:45,701 --> 00:19:47,191
You need to tell him I'm fine.

373
00:19:48,503 --> 00:19:49,970
It's okay if you miss him.

374
00:19:53,242 --> 00:19:54,573
I want my dad.

375
00:19:57,679 --> 00:19:59,408
[SNIFFLING]

376
00:20:03,919 --> 00:20:05,944
[SOBBING]

377
00:20:07,656 --> 00:20:10,386
- We got your page.
- You've gotta give her something.

378
00:20:10,525 --> 00:20:13,050
Seth hasn't come back or called.
She can't stop crying.

379
00:20:13,195 --> 00:20:14,321
We'll prescribe lorazepam.

380
00:20:14,463 --> 00:20:16,988
What you need to do is call Seth
and get him back.

381
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:20,295
Tell him she'll go with him to Florida.

382
00:20:20,435 --> 00:20:23,165
- No.
- I love you more than anything.

383
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:26,103
But you need your son
and you need your grandchildren

384
00:20:26,241 --> 00:20:27,299
more than you need me.

385
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:31,611
Please, talk to him. Tell him she'll go.
Just get him back here.

386
00:20:31,747 --> 00:20:33,772
[SOBBING]

387
00:20:37,586 --> 00:20:40,749
DELL: Hey, I just want you to know
that your dad's outside, waiting.

388
00:20:40,889 --> 00:20:42,015
He wanted to let you know.

389
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:44,318
- What about Dr. Cooper?
- He's gone for the day.

390
00:20:44,459 --> 00:20:46,859
You don't have to worry.
I'm gonna take good care of you.

391
00:20:47,396 --> 00:20:50,695
Once you're asleep,
I'm gonna use this to clean out your lungs.

392
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:52,925
You'll feel much better.
See, who's that?

393
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:56,965
Then we're gonna give Dell
what we took out

394
00:20:57,105 --> 00:21:00,131
to give to Dr. Montgomery
and Dr. Lockhart to test the antibiotics on.

395
00:21:00,542 --> 00:21:02,976
I know it's scary,
but when you wake up, it'll all be over.

396
00:21:03,478 --> 00:21:05,173
I just...

397
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:07,276
I hope it works.

398
00:21:15,590 --> 00:21:18,150
Now, we just need one of these
to stay clear,

399
00:21:18,293 --> 00:21:20,261
and then we'll know
that the bacteria is sensitive

400
00:21:20,395 --> 00:21:21,953
to that combination of antibiotics.

401
00:21:22,597 --> 00:21:24,792
By morning, we should know,
one way or the other.

402
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:27,397
- Wanna grab a bite?
- Actually, I am starved,

403
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:32,030
but I am supposed to meet someone.

404
00:21:32,174 --> 00:21:35,541
- Ah. The cop.
- Yes, the cop.

405
00:21:35,978 --> 00:21:37,809
So you really think
a hot date and fine dining

406
00:21:37,946 --> 00:21:41,382
is better than a guy you can barely stand
and cafeteria mac and cheese?

407
00:21:42,117 --> 00:21:46,918
Well, I do love the mac and cheese.

408
00:21:50,125 --> 00:21:54,027
From a psycho-physiological standpoint,
this is remarkable.

409
00:21:54,162 --> 00:21:55,356
- What is?
- You.

410
00:21:55,497 --> 00:21:58,898
What you do to me.
All day, I couldn't stop thinking about you.

411
00:21:59,034 --> 00:22:01,264
And ever since you called...

412
00:22:02,938 --> 00:22:03,996
[CHUCKLES]

413
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:14,071
- I remember this tasting a lot better.
- I don't know.

414
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:17,552
It takes me back to residency,
you know, when life was simple.

415
00:22:17,686 --> 00:22:20,519
See, I have a hard time picturing you
taking crap from your attending.

416
00:22:20,655 --> 00:22:23,021
- By year two, they all hated me.
- It took them that long?

417
00:22:23,992 --> 00:22:26,119
- Sorry.
- No, it's just...

418
00:22:26,795 --> 00:22:28,285
Yeah, they really hated me.

419
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:31,297
- Ha-ha-ha.
- So did my wife.

420
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,891
- You're married?
- Was.

421
00:22:34,036 --> 00:22:35,264
And the divorce took two years,

422
00:22:35,404 --> 00:22:37,395
four lawyers,
hundreds of thousands of dollars.

423
00:22:37,539 --> 00:22:42,374
We discussed assets, property,
money, the dog,

424
00:22:42,811 --> 00:22:47,145
but not once in all that time
did anyone ever ask me about love.

425
00:22:52,087 --> 00:22:53,145
I'm still bitter.

426
00:22:54,222 --> 00:22:55,621
About the dog.

427
00:22:56,224 --> 00:22:58,158
I get what bitter does.

428
00:22:58,727 --> 00:23:02,219
You know, you have all that love,
and then where does it go?

429
00:23:02,364 --> 00:23:04,628
- You too?
- Member of the club.

430
00:23:06,435 --> 00:23:07,561
So I'm gonna ask this again,

431
00:23:07,702 --> 00:23:10,967
but this time,
pretend you think I'm human.

432
00:23:11,907 --> 00:23:14,432
You wanna maybe have dinner
with me sometime?

433
00:23:15,577 --> 00:23:19,980
- A date?
- I don't think that's a good idea.

434
00:23:20,115 --> 00:23:22,606
Is it because it's me
or because of the cop?

435
00:23:26,922 --> 00:23:28,514
Think about it.

436
00:23:34,830 --> 00:23:36,798
[DOOR OPENS, INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

437
00:23:38,266 --> 00:23:39,699
ADDISON:
Oh.

438
00:23:42,270 --> 00:23:44,704
- Nai?
NAOMI [WHISPERING]: Oh, God.

439
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,774
I am not here.

440
00:23:47,409 --> 00:23:50,640
This is not jealousy.
This is concern for my daughter.

441
00:23:50,779 --> 00:23:53,179
Nai, remember when Maya told you...

442
00:23:54,483 --> 00:23:56,451
Remember when Maya told you
to get a life?

443
00:23:56,585 --> 00:23:57,779
I have a life.

444
00:23:57,919 --> 00:23:58,977
I have a great life.

445
00:23:59,121 --> 00:24:01,749
I'm just standing here on my patio,
in the dark,

446
00:24:01,890 --> 00:24:05,348
spying on your ex,
his girlfriend and your daughter.

447
00:24:13,502 --> 00:24:14,867
[SIGHS]

448
00:24:15,003 --> 00:24:17,528
- I'm being replaced.
- Oh.

449
00:24:17,772 --> 00:24:20,536
Sonya is my replacement.
That's Maya's new mommy.

450
00:24:20,942 --> 00:24:22,341
Shh.

451
00:24:24,412 --> 00:24:26,937
Oh, I'm freaking.

452
00:24:27,082 --> 00:24:28,879
Oh, God. Ignore me, ignore me.

453
00:24:29,017 --> 00:24:30,746
I'm just freaking out.

454
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:32,148
Thank you.

455
00:24:34,022 --> 00:24:35,546
Why aren't you out with Kevin?

456
00:24:35,690 --> 00:24:36,748
[CHUCKLES]

457
00:24:36,892 --> 00:24:39,122
It's not like we're married, Naomi.

458
00:24:39,261 --> 00:24:41,593
I don't have to be with him every night.

459
00:24:42,030 --> 00:24:43,361
I don't have to call or check in.

460
00:24:43,498 --> 00:24:45,432
And if I wanna talk to another man,

461
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,559
it's not like we have promise rings
or anything.

462
00:24:49,337 --> 00:24:50,895
Who is it?

463
00:24:51,039 --> 00:24:53,507
- This other man.
- Oh, no...

464
00:24:54,109 --> 00:24:55,474
[SIGHS]

465
00:24:55,610 --> 00:24:56,872
Wyatt asked me out on a date.

466
00:24:58,346 --> 00:24:59,711
Oh.

467
00:25:00,248 --> 00:25:03,513
He's different than I thought.

468
00:25:04,386 --> 00:25:08,914
Okay, well, can I just say
that you're in a relationship,

469
00:25:09,057 --> 00:25:11,116
so, you know, knees together.

470
00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:13,284
No, I'm not a cheater.

471
00:25:13,428 --> 00:25:16,420
Okay, I've done that.
I'm not gonna do that again.

472
00:25:16,565 --> 00:25:19,398
You know, but I do wanna say yes
to the date.

473
00:25:19,534 --> 00:25:20,592
I just... I don't know.

474
00:25:20,735 --> 00:25:21,793
Should I? I shouldn't.

475
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:25,395
- Should I?
- Oh, God, we are so screwed up.

476
00:25:26,041 --> 00:25:27,406
[SIGHS]
Oh.

477
00:25:39,254 --> 00:25:40,949
This is a nice place.

478
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,988
Crazy humid.

479
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:53,327
Hi.

480
00:25:57,072 --> 00:25:59,097
[AIR HISSING]

481
00:26:02,277 --> 00:26:04,006
Lung cancer.

482
00:26:04,145 --> 00:26:06,204
Doctors gave him six months.

483
00:26:06,348 --> 00:26:08,043
Two years ago.

484
00:26:08,183 --> 00:26:10,151
He went into respiratory failure
last week.

485
00:26:12,087 --> 00:26:13,611
How you holding up?

486
00:26:13,755 --> 00:26:16,189
Well, let's see.

487
00:26:17,025 --> 00:26:18,515
Duke and Landry are downing bourbon.

488
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,287
Mama's taken to her room
with the vapors.

489
00:26:20,428 --> 00:26:23,920
And not a one of them wants any part
